# The `MCRegisterInfo` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcregisterinfo">MCRegisterInfo</a> base class - We assume that the target defines a static array of <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/mcregisterdesc">MCRegisterDesc</a> objects that represent all of the machine registers that the target has. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcregisterinfo">MCRegisterInfo</a> base class - We assume that the target defines a static array of <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/mcregisterdesc">MCRegisterDesc</a> objects that represent all of the machine registers that the target has.

As such, we simply have to track a pointer to this array so that we can turn register number into a register descriptor.

Note this class is designed to be a base class of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetregisterinfo">TargetRegisterInfo</a>, which is the interface used by codegen. However, specific targets <em>should never</em> specialize this class. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcregisterinfo">MCRegisterInfo</a> should only contain getters to access <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/tablegen">TableGen</a> generated physical register data. It must not be extended with virtual methods.

Definition at line 149 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/mc/mcregisterinfo-h">MCRegisterInfo.h</a>.
